1.00	Zalmai_Rasoul	Zalmai Rassoul	Dr. Zalmai Rassoul (born 1923) is a politician in Afghanistan, serving as the Foreign Minister since January 2010 after receiving the confidence vote of the Afghan National Assembly. He previously served as National Security Advisor of the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan, which he held since June 2002. He has accompanied Afghan President Hamid Karzai on all official visits since the establishment of the Interim Administration in 2001.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Zalmai_Rassoul_in_June_2011.jpg/200px-Zalmai_Rassoul_in_June_2011.jpg
